Package com.attivio.client.exposedapi

Class AttivioMBean<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.attivio.client.exposedapi.AttivioMBean<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the object represented by this MBean
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    javax.management.DynamicMBean
    public class AttivioMBean<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements javax.management.DynamicMBean
    A DynamicMBean for exposing attributes and methods via annotations.
    The Attivio MBean class works on methods with three kinds of annotations:
    • Readable and JmxReadable.
      • Method must satisfy validity as defined by JMXUtils.isValidReadable(Method)
    • Writable and JmxWritable.
      • Method must satisfy validity as defined by JMXUtils.isValidWritable(Method)
    • Invokable and JmxInvokable.
      • Method must satisfy validity as defined by JMXUtils.isValidWritable(Method)
    • In cases annotation and methods are not consistent, IllegalArgumentException will be thrown when instantiating this class.

    The fastest way to validate if a Class is valid for its annotation is through calling with the class object.
    new AttivioMBeanInfo(Class)
